From: filamind <abdelmonemawad@hotmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] rc.local: disable upstream auto-update on every boot

The stock IoT Box runs `git remote set-url ... odoo/odoo.git` followed by
`git fetch && git reset --hard FETCH_HEAD` at every boot, which would
silently revert any local patches we apply.

This patch comments out the auto-update block. The IoT Box will still
boot normally, but its `/home/pi/odoo` checkout stays at whatever commit
it shipped with — which is exactly what we want when carrying patches.

If you ever need to re-enable upstream sync, uncomment the block. A
filamind-specific self-update mechanism (pulling from
https://github.com/filamind-app/filamind-iotbox) can be wired in later
without conflicting with this change.

This patch targets the rc.local that ships inside the .img, not a file
in the Odoo source tree, so it is applied at image-build time by
scripts/build-image.sh rather than `git apply`.

---
 etc/rc.local | 18 +++++++++---------
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)

diff --git a/etc/rc.local b/etc/rc.local
--- a/etc/rc.local
+++ b/etc/rc.local
@@ -22,15 +22,15 @@ if [ -f $start_wifi ]; then
   $start_wifi &
 fi

-# Update current branch
-cd /home/pi/odoo
-localbranch=$(sudo -u odoo git symbolic-ref -q --short HEAD)
-localremote=$(sudo -u odoo git config branch.$localbranch.remote)
-
-sudo -u odoo rm -f /home/pi/odoo/.git/shallow.lock
-sudo -u odoo git remote set-url "${localremote}" "https://github.com/odoo/odoo.git"
-
-sudo -u odoo GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY=1 git fetch "${localremote}" "${localbranch}" --depth=1
-sudo -u odoo git reset --hard FETCH_HEAD
+# filamind: upstream auto-update DISABLED to preserve local patches.
+# To re-enable, remove the leading '# ' from the lines below.
+# cd /home/pi/odoo
+# localbranch=$(sudo -u odoo git symbolic-ref -q --short HEAD)
+# localremote=$(sudo -u odoo git config branch.$localbranch.remote)
+#
+# sudo -u odoo rm -f /home/pi/odoo/.git/shallow.lock
+# sudo -u odoo git remote set-url "${localremote}" "https://github.com/odoo/odoo.git"
+#
+# sudo -u odoo GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY=1 git fetch "${localremote}" "${localbranch}" --depth=1
+# sudo -u odoo git reset --hard FETCH_HEAD

 exit 0
